00:01:09.980 --> 00:01:14.330
Pass the tail under the fixed object and loop
it completely around.

00:01:14.330 --> 00:01:22.540
Continue looping until it points back towards
you.

00:01:22.540 --> 00:01:26.500
Pass the tail underneath the main body of
the rope, and poke the tail back through the

00:01:26.500 --> 00:01:30.900
loop that you have created.

00:01:30.900 --> 00:01:34.560
Pull tight.

00:01:34.560 --> 00:01:38.670
Repeat it once more, tail behind the main
rope.

00:01:38.670 --> 00:01:47.460
Bend it back around and poke the tail through
the loop and pull tight.

00:01:47.460 --> 00:01:52.390
An alternative when using a cleat on a pontoon,
is to make a series of loops in a figure of

00:01:52.390 --> 00:01:54.590
eight like this.

00:01:54.590 --> 00:02:24.720
Do this several times finishing off with a
full turn.

